ODE XX. To PYRRHUS.

HAT man is he so mad, as dare From Moorish lioness to tear

Her cubs? My Pyrrhus, dost not see How perilous the task must be? Soon, soon thy beart will fail, and thou Wilt shun the strife awaits thee now ; When through the youths, that throng to stay Her course, she fiercely makes her way, To find Nearchus, peerless youth z Oh rare the struggle, small the ruth, Till one or other yields, and he Her prize, or thine, at last shall be!
